Description: Nature's Flavors Bubble Gum Flavor Powder is Vegan, Kosher, and Gluten Free. This all natural powdered flavor contains no allergens and is excellent in baking applications, dry beverage mixes such as instant coffee, cocoa, protein blends, and is a perfect addition to dry mixes such as pancake, waffle, protein mixes, muffin, beverage and meal replacers. Name: Butterscotch Flavoring Powder
Description:
With a fine powder form, Nature’s Flavors Butterscotch Flavor Powder is ideal for any recipe or application that may call for a dry, powdered flavor. Perfect for products like protein powders, powdered cake or cookie mixes, dry waffle and pancake batters, or even dry beverage mixes, our flavor powders will give you a whole new sense of freedom when it comes to flavoring your recipes.

USAGE GUIDELINES:
Starting usage falls within the range of approximately 1 - 5% of your entire ingredients, but recipes can sometimes need less than 1% as well. Because each recipe is unique, there is no simple formula for how much you will need to flavor a product. It depends on the other ingredients you use, the quantity you are making, what temperature it will be cooked at, and for the length of cooking time (if any). And, because our flavors are concentrated, we suggest that you experiment with our flavor powders, beginning with a small amount and gradually increasing the quantity depending on your optimal finished product.

Name: Coconut Flavor Powder, Natural
Description:
With the smooth and tropical taste of great coconut, you’ll think you’ve landed on a deserted island and gone to pure coconut heaven. What is Coconut Flavor Powder? This natural powdered flavor is excellent in many baking applications, in dry beverage mixes like protein powders, instant coffees, hot cocoa powdered mixes, and more. Moreso, it’s a welcome addition to dry mixes for pancakes, waffles, muffins, and many types of dry, powdered beverage and meal replacers. This flavor is moderately heat stable with a well-rounded taste. Starting usages should be 1-5% depending on a variety of factors. Additionally, it’s not uncommon to see usages below 1% because each recipe or application is varies considerably from the next. Just like with any other ingredient, you will need to experiment a little when first using our Coconut Flavor Powder. Different mixtures of ingredients call for different usages and, essentially, each flavor in our line of flavor powders will call for different ratios as well because they are all different.

Coconut Flavor Powder contains coconut.

Name: Strawberry Flavor Powder, Natural
Description: Perfect to add to any of your dry applications, Nature's Flavors Strawberry Flavor Powder is the essential way to add the mouth-watering taste of freshly picked strawberries. Use our flavor powders in any sort of dry application like powdered mixes for cakes, protein powders, beverage mixes, and more. While our flavor powders are deliciously decadent in every way, Nature's Flavors advises that you first experiment with your original recipes and applications until you determine your ideal ratios. Begin by adding a little of Nature's Flavors Strawberry Flavor Powder and gradually increase dosage in stages to prevent from over-flavoring. Since each recipe is different, experiment with your ingredients along with our flavor powders until you determine the ratios that are best for you. Additionally, keep in mind that our flavor powders are highly concentrated, so a little will go a long way. So, if you're looking for that fresh from the farmers market flavor, look no further and pick Nature's Flavors Strawberry Flavor Powder.

Name: Vanilla Flavor Powder, Natural
Description:
Nature’s Flavors Vanilla Flavor Powder is a natural powdered flavor that is excellent in many kinds of baking applications, dry beverage mixes such as instant coffees, cocoas, protein blends, and more. Additionally, it is a perfect addition to dry mixes for pancakes, waffles, protein powders, muffin mixes, beverages, and meal replacers. Nature’s Flavors Vanilla Flavor Powder is moderately heat stable and brings out a well-rounded flavor in applications. Starting usages should be 1% to 5% of your total ingredients, depending on how long the application is cooked and how high the temperature is. Essentially, you may use even less flavor in some applications due to the nature of the flavor and the makeup of the formula ingredients that you are using. Additionally, it’s not uncommon to see usages of even less than 1% simply because each recipe is different, calls for unique ingredients, and can be cooked for different lengths of time and varying temperatures. Like with any other ingredient, you will first need to experiment with ratios and quantities of our flavor powders until you reach the desired flavor.

Name: Chaste Berry Extract
Description: Chaste berries can be cultivated in subtropical temperatures and can be found on the northeastern coast of the United States. Hundreds of years ago it was used as an anaphrodisiac, hence the name "chaste" berry. It may aid in decreasing the symptoms of PMS by suppressing the production of prolactin. Also, some of its chemical compounds such as Vitexin and Casticin may have some effect on the pituatary gland, which would explain its hormonal impact. It may also be used to treat acne. Women who may be pregnant or are using birth control should not use chasteberry products as it has hormonal impacts.

Name: Vanilla Flavor Extract
Description:
Another Great Recipe by Nature's Flavors Want to learn a quick and delicious recipe using 1234? Below you'll find a wonderful recipe just for that. Of course, you are more than welcome to send us your recipes using 1234.

Baked Caramel Corn #1
Category: Candy
Makes: 24
-6 quarts of Popped corn (about 1-1/4 cp unpopped)
-1 cup of Butter
-2 cups of Brown sugar; packed
-1/2 cups of Corn syrup
-1 teaspoon of Salt
-1/2 teaspoons of Baking soda
-1 teaspoon of Vanilla
-1 cup of Salted nuts
Recipe Preparation Instruction
Heat oven to 250 degrees. Put popped corn in a buttered roasting pan and sprinkle nuts on top. Melt butter in saucepan, stir in brn sugar, cornsyrup and salt. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Boil further without stirring for 5 minutes and then remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, then soda. It will foam at this stage. Stir well. Pour the syrup mixture over the popped corn quickly and mix well. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 mins. Remove from oven, cool and break apart. Store in tightly covered container. THIS CARAMEL CORN IS NOT STICKY.

Name: Vanilla Flavor Extract Aged (2x Fold), Organic
Description:
The entire mixture is aged for up to two weeks in our special aging extractor tanks. During the course of ageing, the extract is continually sampled for peak flavor. We only pull the extract off extraction when it reaches our high standards for taste. The final test prior to filtering is to run the sample on a gas chromatograph which checks for peak purity. You may view our chromatographs and mass spectrometers on our quality control page. Once this testing is complete, the extract is sent to the filtering room where the ground up bean is separated from the liquid extract. The finished vanilla extract may be bottled at this time or put in drums for more ageing.

Good vanilla extract is never rushed but is allowed to age like a fine wine until its time has come. We treat our vanillas this way every time. Our customers have won many awards and honors with our vanilla extract being part of their recipes. Our organic vanilla can be a part of your home recipes or a part of your business. You can buy Nature's Flavors' Organic Vanilla Extract in small quantities and observe the wonderful quality for yourself.

Name: Vanilla Flavor Extract Aged (3x Fold), Organic
Description:
Because of its higher cost many people avoid buying and using Organic Vanilla Extract three fold. But actually it can be more cost affective than a Single Fold Vanilla Extract. You can cut your usage substantially which cuts your Vanilla flavor costs. It is possible to combine both a small amount of single fold Vanilla Extract and Three Fold Vanilla Extract to make a totally unique Vanilla Flavor. When folding or concentrating Vanilla Extract you increase some of the most favorable notes such as creaminess or Chocolate Flavor character. This Organic Vanilla Extract Three Fold works well in Baking applications as a enhancer to other Vanilla Flavors. Start by using a quarter percent in conjunction with Single Fold Vanilla Extract and you will be amazed at the finish flavor of your baked goods. This Three Fold Vanilla Extract is Heat stable due to its concentrated Vanilla components.
This Vanilla Extract Three Fold is also an excellent Vanilla Flavor for dairy products such as Vanilla yogurt, Vanilla Milk, and Vanilla ice cream. Description:
Nature's Flavors' Organic Vanilla Extract is excellent for baking, making ice cream, adding flavor to smoothies and making sodas. This organic vanilla is a family tradition that dates back to the 1930s. We start with the finest Madagascar beans and grind them to a fine mesh. Name: Forest Green Food Coloring, Natural
Description:
Why We Don't Use/Sell Chlorophyll: There are two reasons. First, although chlorophyll is the only pure, natural green color ingredient, the FDA has not yet approved its use as a color additive. Second, even if the FDA gave the go-ahead to sell it, it would not be an effective natural color to use because the color molecules are very fragile and break down extremely easily and quickly. Our natural green color is an effective and all-natural replacement. Replacement of Blue#1+ Yellow #6.

Ingredients: Water, Glycerine, and Vegetable and Plant Extract (no Chlorophyll)

Name: Red Food Coloring (Made with Hibiscus), Natural
Description:
Red Color (Hibiscus) is a Liquid Coloring, made from 100% all-natural ingredients. Packed full of powerful antioxidants, this natural red coloring is heat stable and can be used in most baking applications. Care should be taken to not over cook this color and cool down the finished product as quickly as possible. This natural red color also freezes well and is stable for long term. This color can be used in oil based applications but acts more like a suspension and will not completely dissolve. When making lip balms you can get a red color but you must mix and cool quickly. This natural red color is designed to replace artificial red #40 color. You can mix this natural color with other colors and our organic colors. To make a natural bright red or fire orange color, add some of our organic yellow color or organic orange color. This color is best stored in a cool and dark place. Nature's Flavors natural red color is rich in antioxidants and can be used for for supplementing the body. Just add some to juice or you can add to water with some honey or maple syrup to sweeten it up. Enjoy!

Name: Organic Apricot Brandy Glaze
Description: These Nature's Flavors' Organic Fruit Glazes are designed to give sheen to baked goods, fruit toppings, barbecued food and meat products. They are best used by air brushing but you can also brush them on using a pastry brush and the glazes dry instantly. Did you ever wonder how the pastries at your favorite bakery or store have that shiny sheen to them? This sheen, unless baked on using eggs, is usually achieved by spraying or brushing on a proprietary blend of sugars, fruit purees and natural stabilizers. Nature's Flavors' Organic Fruit Glazes are applied after baking rather than before (unlike egg mixtures which have to be baked on). Spray or brush the glaze on freshly baked pastries to add that special shine just like your favorite bakery does. You can also spray your favorite glaze on ribs just after barbecuing to give them an attractive sheen and a sweeter taste. The glazes dry very quickly and have a slight flavor. However, if you prefer, you can order the Nature's Flavors' Organic Glaze without any added flavor.

Name: Acai Compound, Organic
Description:
The processes for making organic flavors are much the same as for making natural flavors. The ingredients are organic rather than just natural. You start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Nature's Flavors carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients thru these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employee. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Nature's Flavors allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Nature's Flavors has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Description: The processes for making organic flavors are much the same as for making natural flavors. The ingredients are organic rather than just natural. You start by using only certified organic ingredients when available and when not you may use naturals provided they fit with in the definition of natural and only comprise less than 5% of the total amount when calling it 95% organic. When calling it 100% organic you must use only certified organic ingredients and nothing else. Nature's Flavors carries both 95% and 100% certified organic flavors. It is our goal to produce only 100% organic flavor concentrates and extracts as the ingredients become available. In many instances we produce our own organic ingredients to satisfy our strict quality control requirements. Because the industry is still very young the technology's to make these ingredients are still evolving. The only solvents that we use in the development of organic and natural flavors are filtered RO water and organic alcohol. If we can't extract the ingredients thru these methods then we don't do it. Steam distillation is another method we employ. Fortunately this is in most cases the only methods needed to manufacture these unique flavor concentrates and extracts. A simple and common process for making vanilla extract is to take organic vanilla beans and grind them to a pulp then allow them to soak and extract in an organic alcohol/water mixture for a period of time sometimes for up to several months. Normally for a standard organic vanilla extract you would extract for a period of not less than fourteen days. That's how long Nature's Flavors allows its organic vanilla extract to age and extract. This method is common for our citrus and other fruit flavor extracts as well. There are usually some filtering and clarifying techniques that follow the extraction process before being bottled or packaged. There are no chemical residues because there are no chemical solvents used. Many of the organic flavoring ingredients are derived this way first before being incorporated in to water based or oil based organic flavor concentrate. To make the organic flavor concentrates water soluble you must emulsify the oils that were derived and separated from the extraction process or steam distilling and that usually involves using an organic gum or starch and under high pressure and shearing. This process forces the oils and gums to be broken into very small particles and cling to one another with out reforming into there basic building blocks again. The entire process is safe and effective for producing the finest organic flavor oils, flavor concentrates, and flavor extracts. Nature's Flavors has pioneered many of these methods for producing these organic products. We are proud of our flavorings, spices, coffees, and all our organic products. We hope they bring you much enjoyment and satisfaction.

Name: Organic Caramel Apple Dip
Description:
This organic caramel topping tastes like it contains dairy, but is made using a unique blend of all organic ingredients that fools even the most experienced chef. Our organic non-dairy caramel topping is excellent over soy-based ice cream, blended in non-dairy coffee drinks and smoothies, or drizzled over cheesecake. The enjoyment possibilities for this topping are endless. And good news for weight watchers, Nature's Flavors Organic Caramel Dip for Apples is also fat free. As the product name suggests, this organic syrup is perfect for making caramel dipped apples, and great for baking because it is very heat stable. For a true taste treat, here are a couple of suggestions when preparing to enjoy our organic caramel dip on a juicy apple. Heat the caramel topping in a warm water bath up to about 90 degrees. This will make it easier to submerge the apple in the caramel. (The visualization is almost as good as the actual eating!) Chilling the apple before dipping will allow the warm caramel to stick quicker. You're now ready to indulge yourself with another healthy tasty treat from Nature's Flavors. Enjoy! Our Caramel Dip is available in bulk quantities. Please contact us for a price quote.

The production of olive oil dates back to 4500 BC, although some would say evidence exists of even earlier uses. It is often referred to as "liquid gold" since it contains many benefits! Plus it adds delicious flavors to food. Olive oil has been used in medicines and can be added to beauty products for extra moisture to the skin and hair.

Use it in baking and cooking as a healthy way to add flavor and quality to your favorite dishes. You can even use it pure for a tasty addition to your favorite bread! Extra virgin is the healthiest of the olive oils as it has the highest concentration of polyphenols, which may have antimicrobial properties, anti-inflammatory properties and may contribute to better cardiovascular health. It also has the highest level of monounsaturated fats of all oils which may help decrease the amount of "bad" LDL cholesterol levels. Nature's Flavors Organic Extra Virgin Olive Oil is certified organic, so you know there are no harmful chemicals or genetically modified organisms in your product. Organic products are also free from irradiation and sewer sludge, which is beneficial to your health and the environment. Get a head start on a healthier lifestyle today!

Derived from the fruit of the oil palm Elaeis guineensis (native to Central and South America), palm oil has remained the cooking oil of choice for people in Africa, Southeast Asia, and Brazil. Name: Organic Sesame Oil
Description: Our sesame oil is pressed from nutrient-dense sesame seeds, which are exceptionally rich in iron, magnesium, copper, calcium, manganese, and vitamins B and E. With all these benefits packed into a convenient bottle, it is no wonder that sesame oil is one of the earliest known crop-based oil, retaining its extreme popularity for hundreds of years in all parts of Asia. Sesame is native to sub-Saharan Africa, being heavily cultivated during the Indus valley civilization. The benefits of consuming sesame oil are well-known in many Asian cultures-for instance, did you know that In Tamil literature and medicine, sesame oil has been mentioned as the "very good and healthy oil", whereas in the Far East, sesame oil is heavily used to prepare meals for women during postpartum confinement. At Nature's Flavors, we are very happy that this wonderful sesame oil is now available in America. Much research has been done on sesame oil, showing that it possesses antibacterial, antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. There is a study that indicates that sesame oil may play a role in inhibiting the growth of malignant melanomas, and taken regularly, may help in maintaining the balance between good cholesterol (HDL) and bad cholesterol (LDL). This could be attributed to the high prevalence of phytosterols (sterols naturally found in plants) in sesame oil. There is even an experiment done where students who rinsed their mouths with sesame oil showed an 85% reduction in the bacteria that causes gingivitis. Women of ancient Babylon would eat halva, a mixture of sesame oil, honey and sesame seeds to prolong youth and beauty, while Roman soldiers ate the same thing, believing it gave them strength and energy. Indians believe that sesame oil restores moisture to the skin, keeping it soft, flexible and young looking. No description of sesame oil would be complete without mention of sesamin, which is a lignan named after the sesame plant. Sesamin has been used as a dietary fat-reduction supplement and contains significant antioxidant and anticancer properties. Sesamin combined with poly-unsaturated fats found in sesame oil make it potentially very effective for controlling blood pressure and cholesterol levels. So what are you waiting for? Go ahead and try our Nature's Flavors Sesame Oil right now, for you will NOT regret it!!

Name: Organic White Rice Syrup
Description:
What is Organic White Rice Syrup? It’s a healthy, flavorful, and allergen-free alternative to different sweeteners and can make a delightful substitution for sugar, agave, honey, maple syrup, and more. Created from organic white rice, use Organic White Rice Syrup anywhere you would use regular sugar. Great for baking, beverages, desserts, coffee & tea, and more, Nature’s Flavors shares with you the bounty of this delicious natural ingredient. Rice singlehandedly remains the most important grain throughout the world, transcending cultures worldwide as a main source of sustenance and nutrition. In order to prolong the shelf life, organic white rice has its husk, bran, and germ removed. After milling, the rice is polished, giving it its shiny, white characteristic. White rice is then fermented, strained, and filtered to obtain the perfect consistency found in Nature's Flavors Organic White Rice Syrup.

Name: Cranberry Juice Powder
Description: They are a large part of cultivated food products in the U.S. There are four different species of cranberries, all of which are used in food products. They are related to blueberries and are also called mossberries in Canada. The Native Americans first used cranberries for a variety of things such as: food, medicine and dye. Cranberries are usually harvested in the fall, between September and November. If eaten raw, cranberries can be very sour and bitter; therefore, it is best to enjoy them in your favorite products, such as Nature's Flavors Cranberry Juice Powder and Purified Cranberry Fruit Juice Extract Powder. Nature's Flavors Cranberry Juice Powder and Purified Cranberry Fruit Juice Extract Powder contain cranberry, which is an excellent source of vitamin C, fiber and other nutrients. They may inhibit plaque formation by Streptococcus mutans, which is a bacteria that causes dental caries (Cavities). They also may be helpful in the prevention of recurring urinary tract infections in woman by preventing bacteria from adhering to the body. Cranberry also contains high amounts of salicylic acid, which can reduce swelling and prevent blood clots. Cranberry may interact with the drug warfarin, which is used to slow blood clotting, so be careful with your cranberry intake if you are also taking warfarin. Nature's Flavors Cranberry Juice Powder and Cranberry Fruit Juice Extract Powder are great ways to add wonderful tasting cranberry to your favorite drinks and other recipes, so why not try some today!!

Name: Dried Egg Yolk Powder
Description:
By using powdered egg yolks, there is no mess in separating the whites from the yolks and they require no refrigeration. The shelf life of dried egg yolks is about one year with no refrigeration required.

When storing powdered egg yolks keep them in air-tight resealable containers away from heat or large temperature swings. It is also important to keep dried egg products away from direct sunlight or artificial light as that will cause the eggs to oxidize quickly. This is because of their high-fat content.

Nature's Flavors dried powdered egg yolks are excellent for cooking, Baking, and adding fats to foods where fat is necessary to achieve a smooth textured product.

An example would be in making sauces such as hollandaise, or making a powdered custard mix, or a powdered ice cream mix like gelato where additional fat is a must. They create a smooth texture and good mouth feel by controlling the crystallization of the water molecules. The dried egg yolks are pasteurized so they are very stable for long periods of time.

When storing dried powdered egg yolks or egg whites you should keep them in air-tight resalable containers away from heat or large temperature swings. It is also important to keep dried egg products away from direct sunlight or artificial light as that will cause the eggs to oxidize quickly.

This is especially true for dried egg yolks due to their high-fat content. Using powdered egg yolks or egg whites in cooking applications produces good clean results consistently time after time that's why manufacturers overwhelmingly approve of dried egg products over the alternative of having to crack and separate the egg yolks from the egg whites. Also, you don't have to worry about potential bacterial contamination as once they are pasteurized and kept dry until used they are usually free of this problem. Once you hydrate them than they must be used right away. Shelf life of dried egg yolks is about one year or more with no refrigeration required. Dried egg yolks are an excellent emulsifier especially in the formation of mayonnaise, or salad dressings or any food where water and oil will need to be mixed together.

Using powdered eggs yolks in cooking applications produces good clean results consistently time after time which is why manufacturers overwhelmingly approve of dried egg products over the alternative of having to crack and separate the egg yolks from the egg whites.

If you need to add a bit of fat to foods to achieve a smooth textured product, egg yolk powder will do that for you. Examples of this would be in making Hollandaise sauce, or when making gelato where additional fat is a must. They create a smooth texture and good-mouth feel by controlling the crystallization of the water molecules.

How to use the powdered egg yolk – here's the conversion:

  • 3 teaspoons equals 1 tablespoon
  • One medium egg contains about 3 teaspoons of egg yolk in it. (One teaspoon of dried egg yolk power plus 2 ? teaspoons of water will give you 3 ? teaspoons of egg yolk, just about the yolk of one medium size egg yolk.)
  • One large egg contains about 4 teaspoons of egg yolk in it.
  • An extra-large egg contains about 4 ? or more teaspoons of egg yolk in it, depending on the exact size of the egg.

Recipes
Dried powdered egg yolks are an excellent emulsifier to use in salad dressings, homemade mayonnaise, an egg glaze for pie crust, egg drop soup, Hollandaise sauce, crepes and in any food where water and oil will need to be mixed together. These powdered egg yolks also make a nice hair conditioner (1 yolk) in the final rinse after shampooing, leave in a minute or two and rinse thoroughly, and in a facial mask (1-2 yolks), leave on your face up to 5 minutes and rinse. It will tighten your pores and give you an instant face "lift."

Attention customers!
Our Gallon Jags have a cup with a Seal. The Seal is composed of a Starch Base and may dissolve over time. This will not harm or affect the Flavor in any way.
Citrus Based Flavors may dissolve this seal faster.

Comforting, tasty, and filled with the flavors of cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves, you’ll never be in search of a healthy alternative again. For Linda Baking Mixes are carefully crafted with you in mind. As the world’s focus is changing to more of a healthy perspective, our baking mixes are changing right along with it. With a focus on whole, nutrient-dense ingredients and lowering the amount of unnecessary sugars we have in our regular day-to-day lives, we’re proud to present you with a mix that is great for so many of life’s occasions, so you can serve a dessert that is superior on so many levels. All you need to do is simply add water and oil to this ready-to-bake mix, and you’ll be well on your way to pumpkin spice bliss in no time at all.

Ingredients: water, sunflower oil, erythritol powder, lupine flour, tapioca starch, white rice flour, drum dried pumpkin flakes, ground cinnamon, baking powder, xanthan gum, baking soda, salt, acacia gum, psyllium husks

Name: Black Cherry Syrup, Organic
Description:
This syrup can be used in so many ways. One of its most popular uses is in coffee as a flavor and sweetener. In an 8-ounce cup of coffee, add 1 to 2 teaspoons of syrup (depending on your sweetness preference).

If you have a way to make homemade ice cream, then it will make the greatest black cherry-flavored ice cream you have ever tasted. Simply add one tablespoon syrup to 16 ounces of half-and-half and mix thoroughly. Then add 1 cup of organic corn syrup or honey. Finally, add 1 teaspoon of Nature’s Flavors’ Organic Vanilla Extract, mix and allow it to chill for 1 to 2 hours. Once chilled, you can begin adding the mixture to your automatic ice cream maker. This recipe works great in most automatic ice cream makers like the Cuisinart™ frozen yogurt, ice cream, and sorbet maker.

It's also excellent for baking. It is very heat stable and will bake well without a significant flavor loss. It is excellent in cookies, cakes, and icings. You can add a little to puddings and custards for a little extra flair.
